com.SoftWoehr.FIJI.base.desktop.shell
Class ControlFlowElement

java.lang.Object
  |
  +--com.SoftWoehr.FIJI.base.desktop.shell.ControlFlowElement
All Implemented Interfaces:
SoftWoehr, verbose
public class ControlFlowElement
extends java.lang.Object
implements SoftWoehr, verbose

ControlFlowElement wrappers a Semantic pushed on the control flow stack along with information about the context when the entry was pushed. Definitions may nest and the current definition is pushed to support this, but the real nice thing aside from the marginally useful ability to nest definitions is that it's easy for the compiler to know a definition was messed up when it doesn't find a Definition control flow element on popping the control flow stack.
